nd just let your hamster run around on your hands how long does it take for them to get used to you well it really does has to do with the bonding and your hamster and trust so handeling your hamster everyday for about minutes will create a bond and trust and will reduce any biting i hope that this answers all of your questions thanks and good luck with your new hamster future vet Hamster Guinea pig Breastfeeding Teen Girl Squad Cat Sin City Theory of conduct Atkins Nutritional Approach Obesity Domestic rabbit Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Butters Stotch Tofu Ron and Fez Pet skunk Trapping Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Social rule Animal communication Equine conformation Professional wrestling match types Mutual fund Bass guitar Violin Coprophagia Tocopherol W.I.T.C.H. Mattress Flatulence Dog training Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Ferret Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Dog Golden Hamster Upholstery The Long Game Internet phenomenon Russian joke Brand Hypoglycemia Singlish Stewie Griffin: The Untold Story! The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy Stuttering Vegeta Soft drink CPU cache Food Garfield Textile manufacturing Happy Tree Friends Folic acid Urinary incontinence Dairy Drill bit Professional wrestling throws Comanche Chocolate Tooth enamel Money Milton H. Erickson Omega-3 fatty acid Bart Simpson Hazing Knife Tire Trademark Codename: Kids Next Door Brown Bear Jumpstart 3rd Grade Ramen Extreme Programming Eutheism, dystheism, and maltheism Phoebe Buffay's songs 2000 Australian Grand Prix Hide and Seek (Stargate Atlantis) Floppy disk Richard Chase Opportunity rover timeline for 2004 February Main characters of Fullmetal Alchemist "Weird Al" Yankovic The Fairly OddParents Babe Ruth EastEnders Criticism of government response to Hurricane Katrina 613 mitzvot Healthy eating Chicken Ultraviolet Egg (food) Sharia Minor characters in Teen Titans (animated series) Sonic the Hedgehog 2 Chili con carne Avenue Q Prince Edmund (Blackadder) 